sentences: Jason James Desiata Dy (born June 19, 1990) is a Filipino singer, songwriter and occasional actor.
Dy was invited onstage by David Foster to perform with him during his HitMan tour at the Smart Araneta Coliseum, Manila, August 18, 2015.
Dy's eponymous album, Jason Dy, was released by MCA Universal on September 4, 2015.
A deluxe edition with additional original compositions was released October 2016.
March 2017, Dy received a gold record award from MCA Music for his Jason Dy album at a celebration at Robinson's Galleria.
In May 2017, Dy went on a Malaysian promo tour for his latest single "Nothing Like Cinta Ini" with Malaysian singer Fazura.
Jason Dy was born on June 19, 1990, in Cebu City, Philippines but was raised by his parents in Butuan City.
In 2003, his parents separated; they were granted an annulment in 2014.
